478
00:42:07,350 --> 00:42:09,350
- Who the fuck is that?
- You don't know him?

479
00:42:09,430 --> 00:42:11,060
No! Should I?

480
00:42:11,140 --> 00:42:12,770
Wait a minute.

481
00:42:12,850 --> 00:42:15,310
- Is thatJohn G.?
- I don't think so.

482
00:42:15,400 --> 00:42:18,690
- You don't think so? You didn't write it down?
- I might've fallen asleep before I did.

483
00:42:18,770 --> 00:42:20,770
For Christ's sakes!

484
00:42:22,070 --> 00:42:23,610
Ask him.

485
00:42:27,700 --> 00:42:29,240
What's your name?

486
00:42:29,330 --> 00:42:30,330
Your name.

487
00:42:30,910 --> 00:42:32,740
- Dodd.
- Who did this to you?

488
00:42:32,830 --> 00:42:35,410
- What?
- Who did this to you?

489
00:42:35,500 --> 00:42:37,000
You did.

490
00:42:40,250 --> 00:42:43,510
- I'm not gonna help you kill that guy.
- No, just let me think for a minute.

491
00:42:49,300 --> 00:42:51,720
Okay, Natalie. Who's Natalie?

492
00:42:51,810 --> 00:42:53,270
- Natalie who?
- Why?

493
00:42:53,350 --> 00:42:56,440
- Maybe I know her.
- Look. We gotta get him out of here.

494
00:42:57,350 --> 00:42:58,980
All right, all right.

495
00:43:00,110 --> 00:43:02,070
He's gotta have a car, right?

496
00:43:02,150 --> 00:43:05,740
We take him down to his car, tell him to get
the fuck out of town or we're gonna kill him.

497
00:43:05,820 --> 00:43:07,900
We can't walk him out of here
tied up and bleeding.

498
00:43:07,990 --> 00:43:10,450
- How the fuck did you get him up here?
- I don't know.

499
00:43:10,530 --> 00:43:12,490
You don't know.

500
00:43:14,660 --> 00:43:16,580
Yes, I do. This is not my room.

501
00:43:16,660 --> 00:43:18,460
It must be his room.
Great! Let's go.

502
00:43:18,540 --> 00:43:20,500
- No, no. We can't just leave him here.
- Why not?

503
00:43:20,590 --> 00:43:25,130
Because the maid's gonna walk in. She'll
see him, call the cops. He can ID us.

504
00:43:27,010 --> 00:43:28,840
Okay. We untie him...

505
00:43:28,930 --> 00:43:31,800
we clean him up, and we march him
out of here with a gun in his back.

506
00:43:31,890 --> 00:43:33,850
A gun. Why would I have a gun?

507
00:43:35,350 --> 00:43:38,690
It must be his. I don't think
they'd let someone like me carry a gun.

508
00:43:40,230 --> 00:43:41,520
Fucking hope not.

509
00:43:48,860 --> 00:43:50,360
Which one?

510
00:43:53,370 --> 00:43:55,910
We should probably steal his car.
You know, teach him a lesson.

511
00:43:56,000 --> 00:43:56,950
Shut up.

512
00:43:57,040 --> 00:43:59,460
That's all right for you to say.
You're the one with the Jag.

513
00:43:59,540 --> 00:44:02,420
Get in.
I'm gonna ride with him. You follow us.

514
00:44:02,500 --> 00:44:04,420
Give me your keys.

515
00:44:04,500 --> 00:44:06,710
Take your own car.

516
00:44:34,660 --> 00:44:37,700
- So was he scared?
- Yeah. I think it was your sinister mustache.

517
00:44:37,790 --> 00:44:40,500
Fuck you.
You should have stolen his car.

518
00:44:40,580 --> 00:44:43,630
- Why? What's wrong with this one?
- Nothing. You want to trade?

519
00:44:46,960 --> 00:44:49,050
So what do you do now?

520
00:44:49,130 --> 00:44:51,590
I'm going to find out
what the fuck that was all about.

521
00:44:59,180 --> 00:45:01,600
Natalie, right?
Who the fuck is Dodd?

522
00:45:04,230 --> 00:45:07,270
Sammy's wife was crippled
by the cost of supporting him...

523
00:45:07,360 --> 00:45:09,440
and fighting the company's decision.

524
00:45:11,320 --> 00:45:13,610
But it wasn't the money that got to her.

525
00:45:13,700 --> 00:45:16,700
- <i>I never said that Sammy was faking.</i>
- Listen. I have an idea.

526
00:45:16,780 --> 00:45:18,410
Sammy, I have an idea.

527
00:45:18,490 --> 00:45:21,160
<i>Just that his problem was mental,
not physical.</i>

528
00:45:21,250 --> 00:45:24,500
I want you to have a pen
in your pocket, okay?

529
00:45:24,580 --> 00:45:27,130
- <i>But she couldn't understand.</i>
- You're gonna have a pad in your pocket.

530
00:45:27,210 --> 00:45:29,210
- I did something wrong?
- You did something wrong!

531
00:45:29,300 --> 00:45:32,420
We're gonna deal with it.
We're gonna try harder.

532
00:45:32,510 --> 00:45:34,630
<i>She looks into his eyes
and sees the same person.</i>

533
00:45:34,720 --> 00:45:37,850
<i>If it's not a physical problem,
he should just snap out of it.</i>

534
00:45:37,930 --> 00:45:39,640
- Ellen called!
- Ellen called?

535
00:45:40,810 --> 00:45:44,350
- Ellen can't come today! Ellen can't come!
- Okay. I'm sorry!

536
00:45:44,440 --> 00:45:47,560
- I'm sorry. I'm trying. I'm sorry.
- Try harder!

537
00:45:51,320 --> 00:45:55,450
So good old Leonard Shelby from the insurance
company gives her the seed of doubt...

538
00:45:56,030 --> 00:45:58,160
just like he gave it to the doctors.

539
00:45:58,950 --> 00:46:01,660
But I never said that he was faking.
I never said that.

540
00:46:08,000 --> 00:46:10,380
I don't feel drunk.

541
00:47:22,580 --> 00:47:24,080
- Hello?
- Shit.

542
00:47:24,160 --> 00:47:25,580
Housekeeping.

543
00:47:25,660 --> 00:47:27,750
- Not right now.
- I'm sorry.

544
00:47:51,060 --> 00:47:51,940
Okay.

545
00:47:56,650 --> 00:48:00,780
"Dodd. Put him onto Teddy
or just get rid of him for Natalie."

546
00:48:06,830 --> 00:48:07,950
Dodd.

547
00:48:13,130 --> 00:48:16,500
Get rid of him. Ask Natalie.

548
00:48:18,760 --> 00:48:20,010
Teddy, Teddy.

549
00:48:31,440 --> 00:48:33,690
<i>Leave your number.
You know what to do.</i>

550
00:48:33,770 --> 00:48:35,940
Yeah. This is a message for Teddy.

551
00:48:36,030 --> 00:48:38,070
I'm at the Mountcrest Inn
of Fifth Street, room six.

552
00:48:38,150 --> 00:48:41,150
I need you to come over
as soon as you get this. It's important.

553
00:48:41,240 --> 00:48:43,490
This is Leonard. Thanks. Bye.

554
00:48:47,790 --> 00:48:49,290
Fuck.

555
00:48:58,670 --> 00:49:02,340
What Mrs. Jankis didn't understand was that
you can't bully someone into remembering.

556
00:49:02,430 --> 00:49:04,430
The more pressure you're under,
the harder it gets.

557
00:49:07,180 --> 00:49:09,180
Then call me back?

558
00:49:31,120 --> 00:49:32,910
Okay. What am I doing?

559
00:49:35,250 --> 00:49:36,880
I'm chasing this guy.

560
00:49:39,460 --> 00:49:42,130
No. He's chasing me.

561
00:50:04,950 --> 00:50:06,570
Fuck.

562
00:50:09,990 --> 00:50:12,290
"Dodd. White guy.

563
00:50:12,370 --> 00:50:14,330
Mountcrest Inn on Fifth Street."

564
00:50:15,290 --> 00:50:17,960
I'll get the jump on you, you fucker.

565
00:50:54,500 --> 00:50:55,960
Fuck.

566
00:50:58,630 --> 00:50:59,960
Sorry.

567
00:51:33,490 --> 00:51:35,500
I need a weapon.

568
00:51:38,750 --> 00:51:39,920
This'll do.

569
00:52:03,650 --> 00:52:06,070
I don't feel drunk.

570
00:52:48,110 --> 00:52:49,740
Do I know this guy?

571
00:52:51,200 --> 00:52:52,740
He seems to know me.

572
00:52:57,580 --> 00:52:59,000
What the fuck?

573
00:53:12,590 --> 00:53:14,760
- I like your car.
- Thank you.

574
00:53:14,850 --> 00:53:16,850
- Where'd you get it?
- Are you interested in buying one?

575
00:53:17,470 --> 00:53:19,390
I haven't made a strong enough
impression on you?

576
00:53:19,480 --> 00:53:21,480
I wouldn't be too hard on yourself.

577
00:53:32,200 --> 00:53:34,110
Okay. What am I doing?

578
00:53:44,790 --> 00:53:46,500
Who is this?

579
00:55:05,120 --> 00:55:07,040
Ouch. Cut it out.

580
00:55:38,820 --> 00:55:41,990
- How can you read that again?
- It's good.

581
00:55:43,240 --> 00:55:45,120
Yeah, but you've read it,
like, a thousand times.

582
00:55:45,200 --> 00:55:46,790
I enjoy it.

583
00:55:47,960 --> 00:55:50,790
I always thought the pleasure of a book
was in wanting to know what happens next.

584
00:55:50,880 --> 00:55:52,590
Don't be a prick.

585
00:55:52,670 --> 00:55:55,250
I'm not reading it to annoy you.
I enjoy it.

586
00:55:56,380 --> 00:55:58,880
Just let me read, please.

587
00:56:09,730 --> 00:56:12,100
Probably tried this before.

588
00:56:14,230 --> 00:56:17,070
Probably burned truckloads of your stuff.

589
00:56:19,610 --> 00:56:21,610
Can't remember to forget you.

590
00:56:39,970 --> 00:56:41,010
Yeah.

591
00:56:41,590 --> 00:56:42,800
Uh-huh.

592
00:56:44,640 --> 00:56:47,770
Sir, that'd certainly be in keeping
with some of my own discoveries.

593
00:56:48,350 --> 00:56:51,730
I was hoping for a little more on the
drugs angle. Can you hang on a sec?

594
00:57:00,320 --> 00:57:03,570
The police report mentioned the drugs
found in the car outside my house.

595
00:57:03,660 --> 00:57:05,740
The car was stolen,
but his prints were all over it.

596
00:57:05,830 --> 00:57:08,540
I got friends in the department.
They gave me a copy of it.

597
00:57:08,620 --> 00:57:10,910
I dealt with the police a lot
in my insurance job.

598
00:57:11,000 --> 00:57:15,080
With my condition, it's really tough.
I can't keep it all in mind at once.

599
00:57:15,170 --> 00:57:18,420
I have to summarize the different sections.
And there's pages missing.

600
00:57:18,510 --> 00:57:20,670
I guess I've been trying to log them all.

601
00:57:20,760 --> 00:57:23,010
I don't know why these are crossed out.

602
00:57:23,090 --> 00:57:25,010
But they weren't even looking for John G.

603
00:57:25,100 --> 00:57:27,850
The stuff they found in the car fit in with
what they believed had happened...

604
00:57:27,930 --> 00:57:29,850
so they didn't chase any of it up.

605
00:58:05,970 --> 00:58:07,050
Honey.

606
00:58:09,560 --> 00:58:11,350
Honey, it's late.

607
00:58:33,580 --> 00:58:35,500
Everything okay?

608
00:58:53,140 --> 00:58:54,600
You okay in there?

609
00:58:58,110 --> 00:58:59,810
Was it good for you?

610
00:59:02,030 --> 00:59:04,940
What?
Was I supposed to lock the door?

611
00:59:05,860 --> 00:59:06,950
No.

612
00:59:09,370 --> 00:59:11,280
I'd like you to leave now.

613
00:59:32,310 --> 00:59:35,350
There's something about the drugs stashed
in the car that doesn't ring true for me.

614
00:59:36,020 --> 00:59:37,940
Because the police claim
the guy was an addict...

615
00:59:38,020 --> 00:59:40,020
needing money to score,
which I think is bullshit...

616
00:59:40,110 --> 00:59:43,360
'cause he's not gonna go breaking into places
while he's still got a stash that big.

617
00:59:44,320 --> 00:59:46,990
I think John G. left it there
or planted it there.

618
00:59:48,820 --> 00:59:50,820
How do you know that?

619
00:59:52,280 --> 00:59:54,290
Shit. That's true. It fits.

620
00:59:55,000 --> 00:59:56,950
So he's a dealer.

621
00:59:57,620 --> 00:59:59,540
Hang on a sec.

622
01:00:09,680 --> 01:00:11,680
Now we're getting somewhere.

623
01:00:11,760 --> 01:00:13,350
"Discount Inn."

624
01:01:07,320 --> 01:01:09,530
Yeah, okay. Blonde's fine.

625
01:01:11,910 --> 01:01:14,030
That's what they say.

626
01:01:14,120 --> 01:01:16,240
The Discount Inn. 304.

627
01:01:17,240 --> 01:01:18,290
Leonard.

628
01:01:19,700 --> 01:01:21,120
What then?

629
01:01:21,710 --> 01:01:24,420
We just go to bed.
You wait for me to fall asleep.

630
01:01:24,500 --> 01:01:26,590
You go into the bathroom
and you slam the door.

631
01:01:26,670 --> 01:01:29,210
- Slam it?
- Yeah. Loud enough to wake me up.

632
01:01:29,300 --> 01:01:31,260
- And that's it?
- That's it.

633
01:01:34,050 --> 01:01:37,100
First I just need you to put
these things around the room.

634
01:01:40,140 --> 01:01:43,270
Just pretend they're your things
and that this is your bedroom.

635
01:01:55,070 --> 01:01:59,950
- Should I wear it?
- No. Just like you took it off or something.

636
01:02:02,910 --> 01:02:05,330
I don't want you to use it.
I'm sorry.

637
01:02:07,040 --> 01:02:09,130
I just mean put them
around the room...

638
01:02:09,210 --> 01:02:11,800
as if they were your things.

639
01:02:16,300 --> 01:02:18,300
Whatever gets you off.

640
01:02:42,700 --> 01:02:44,830
I can't blame the cops
for not taking me seriously.

641
01:02:44,910 --> 01:02:47,250
This is a difficult condition
for people to understand.

642
01:02:47,330 --> 01:02:50,590
Look at SammyJankis.
His own wife couldn't deal with it.

643
01:02:50,670 --> 01:02:53,210
I told you about how she tried
to get him to snap out of it.

644
01:02:53,300 --> 01:02:56,630
Eventually she came to see me at the
office. I found out all kinds of shit.

645
01:02:57,140 --> 01:02:59,600
<i>She told me about life with Sammy,
how she treated him.</i>

646
01:02:59,680 --> 01:03:01,140
Thank you for seeing me.

647
01:03:01,220 --> 01:03:03,970
It got to the point where she'd get Sammy
to hide food all around the house.

648
01:03:04,060 --> 01:03:05,810
Then she'd stop feeding him
to see if his hunger...

649
01:03:05,890 --> 01:03:07,850
would make him remember
where he'd hidden the food.

650
01:03:10,190 --> 01:03:12,820
<i>She wasn't a cruel person.
She just wanted old Sammy back.</i>

651
01:03:12,900 --> 01:03:16,700
Mr. Shelby, you know all about Sammy
and you've decided that he's faking.

652
01:03:16,780 --> 01:03:19,410
Mrs. Jankis, the company's position
isn't that Sammy is faking anything...

653
01:03:19,490 --> 01:03:21,410
just that his condition
can't be shown to be...

654
01:03:21,490 --> 01:03:24,950
I just want to know
what your honest opinion about Sammy is.

655
01:03:25,040 --> 01:03:27,960
We shouldn't even be talking like this
while the case is still open to appeal.

656
01:03:28,040 --> 01:03:31,290
- I'm not appealing the decision.
- Then why are you here?

657
01:03:31,380 --> 01:03:33,840
Try to understand.
When I look at Sammy...

658
01:03:33,920 --> 01:03:37,380
I don't see some... vegetable.

659
01:03:37,470 --> 01:03:39,550
I see my same old Sammy.

660
01:03:41,720 --> 01:03:46,140
What do you think that's like for me to suspect
he might be imagining this whole problem...

661
01:03:46,230 --> 01:03:48,310
and that if I just could
say the right thing...

662
01:03:48,400 --> 01:03:51,190
he'd snap out of it
and go back to being normal?

663
01:03:56,740 --> 01:04:00,530
If I knew that my old
Sammy were truly gone...

664
01:04:00,620 --> 01:04:04,740
then I could say good-bye
and start loving this new Sammy.

665
01:04:06,750 --> 01:04:09,580
As long as I have doubt,
I can't say good-bye and move on.

666
01:04:09,670 --> 01:04:11,420
What do you want from me?

667
01:04:11,500 --> 01:04:14,670
I want you to forget the company
you work for for 30 seconds...

668
01:04:14,750 --> 01:04:18,420
and tell me if you really believe
that Sammy's faking his condition.

669
01:04:19,590 --> 01:04:23,680
I need to know...
what you honestly believe.

670
01:04:29,020 --> 01:04:32,600
I believe that Sammy should be physically
capable of making new memories.

671
01:04:40,530 --> 01:04:41,610
Thank you.

672
01:04:44,280 --> 01:04:47,200
I thought I helped her. I thought
she just needed some kind of answer.

673
01:04:47,290 --> 01:04:49,290
I didn't think it was important
what the answer was...

674
01:04:50,120 --> 01:04:52,120
just that she had one to believe.

675
01:05:07,220 --> 01:05:10,060
- A car this nice you should lock.
- Who the fuck are you?

676
01:05:10,140 --> 01:05:12,480
- Teddy, your buddy.
- Prove it.

677
01:05:12,560 --> 01:05:16,190
Sammy. Remember Sammy?
You told me about Sammy!

678
01:05:17,730 --> 01:05:19,230
Geez!

679
01:05:19,320 --> 01:05:21,240
What the fuck are you doing in my car?

680
01:05:21,320 --> 01:05:23,450
What, your sense of humor
went with the memory?

681
01:05:23,530 --> 01:05:26,490
- Do you even know why you're here?
- Unfinished business.

682
01:05:26,580 --> 01:05:28,950
Lenny, let me inform you.

683
01:05:29,040 --> 01:05:31,410
Your business here is very much finished.

684
01:05:31,500 --> 01:05:34,500
- You're still here because of Natalie.
- Who's Natalie?

685
01:05:34,580 --> 01:05:37,710
Schmuck, whose house do you think
you just walked out of?

686
01:05:40,090 --> 01:05:43,510
That's right. Take a look at your pictures.
I bet you got one of her.

687
01:05:45,430 --> 01:05:47,720
Nice shot, Leibovitz.

688
01:05:48,390 --> 01:05:51,560
You'll wanna make a note.
You can't trust her.

689
01:05:51,640 --> 01:05:53,020
Yeah? Why's that?

690
01:05:53,100 --> 01:05:56,360
Because by now she's taken
a look at this suit and the car...

691
01:05:56,440 --> 01:06:00,820
and she's starting to figure out ways
of turning the situation to her advantage.

692
01:06:01,780 --> 01:06:04,240
She's already got you staying
with her, for Christ's sakes.

693
01:06:04,320 --> 01:06:07,910
You can't go back in there.
Let me give you the name of a motel.

694
01:06:07,990 --> 01:06:11,870
- You're lucky I ran into you. That broad's bad news.
- What do you mean, "bad news"?

695
01:06:11,960 --> 01:06:14,250
She's involved with drugs.

696
01:06:14,330 --> 01:06:16,630
Look. These. You see these?

697
01:06:16,710 --> 01:06:18,670
This is the bar where she works.

698
01:06:18,750 --> 01:06:20,800
Her boyfriend's a drug dealer.

699
01:06:20,880 --> 01:06:23,510
She takes orders for him,
arranges meets.

700
01:06:23,590 --> 01:06:26,470
He writes messages on the back of these.

701
01:06:26,550 --> 01:06:29,100
Then she slips him the answers
when she serves him his drinks.

702
01:06:29,180 --> 01:06:33,270
- Why should I care?
- Because when she gets jammed up...

703
01:06:33,350 --> 01:06:35,520
she's gonna use you to protect herself.

704
01:06:35,600 --> 01:06:36,810
From who?

705
01:06:36,900 --> 01:06:39,650
Guys are gonna wanna know
what happened to her boyfriend.

706
01:06:39,730 --> 01:06:43,280
Guys are gonna come after her.
Somebody's gotta pay, Lenny.

707
01:06:43,360 --> 01:06:46,410
Somebody always pays.
Maybe she'll make it you.

708
01:06:46,490 --> 01:06:49,990
Oh, yeah?
Maybe she'll make it you. Is that it?

709
01:06:50,080 --> 01:06:51,990
You worried that she's gonna use me
against you?

710
01:06:52,080 --> 01:06:54,080
- No.
- Why not?

711
01:06:54,790 --> 01:06:57,420
Because she doesn't know who I am.

712
01:06:58,420 --> 01:07:00,960
- Why are you following me?
- Maybe I wanna help.

713
01:07:01,750 --> 01:07:04,970
She doesn't know anything about
your investigation, okay, Einstein?

714
01:07:05,050 --> 01:07:07,720
So write this down.

715
01:07:07,800 --> 01:07:12,470
When she offers to help,
it'll be for her own reasons.

716
01:07:12,560 --> 01:07:17,350
I'm not lying.
Take my pen. Write this down.

