- Thanks.

964
01:26:34,220 --> 01:26:36,590
It's completely fucked
because nobody believes you.

965
01:26:37,800 --> 01:26:41,060
It's amazing what a little brain damage
will do for your credibility.

966
01:26:41,140 --> 01:26:43,930
I guess it's some kind of poetic justice
for not believing Sammy.

967
01:26:44,020 --> 01:26:46,190
You know the truth
about my condition, Officer?

968
01:26:47,020 --> 01:26:49,020
You don't know anything.

969
01:26:49,110 --> 01:26:51,280
You feel angry, you don't know why.

970
01:26:51,360 --> 01:26:54,110
You feel guilty, you have no idea why.

971
01:26:54,950 --> 01:26:57,570
You could do anything and not have
the faintest idea 10 minutes later.

972
01:26:57,660 --> 01:27:00,030
Like Sammy.
What if I've done something like Sammy?

973
01:27:00,740 --> 01:27:04,000
I didn't tell you what happened
to Sammy and his wife?

974
01:27:05,750 --> 01:27:08,920
She came to see me at my office. I thought
she was trying to catch me off guard...

975
01:27:09,000 --> 01:27:11,920
<i>so I didn't tell her what I really thought,
but I never said that he was faking...</i>

976
01:27:12,010 --> 01:27:13,920
<i>just that his condition was mental,
not physical.</i>

977
01:27:14,010 --> 01:27:16,970
<i>I found out later that she went home
and gave Sammy his final exam.</i>

978
01:27:18,680 --> 01:27:21,640
Sammy? It's time for my shot.

979
01:27:37,610 --> 01:27:39,620
<i>She knew beyond a doubt that he loved her.</i>

980
01:27:40,780 --> 01:27:42,740
<i>So she found a way to test him.</i>

981
01:27:55,470 --> 01:27:59,050
Sammy. It's time for my shot.

982
01:28:09,020 --> 01:28:11,060
<i>She really thought she'd call his bluff.</i>

983
01:28:11,150 --> 01:28:12,650
There you go.

984
01:28:13,230 --> 01:28:17,070
<i>Or she just didn't wanna live
with the things she'd put him through.</i>

985
01:28:27,040 --> 01:28:28,040
Sammy.

986
01:28:30,210 --> 01:28:32,330
It's time for my shot.

987
01:28:37,800 --> 01:28:39,590
It won't hurt.

988
01:29:23,720 --> 01:29:25,760
<i>She went into a coma and never recovered.</i>

989
01:29:26,930 --> 01:29:30,020
<i>Sammy couldn't understand
or explain what happened.</i>

990
01:29:32,310 --> 01:29:34,230
He's been in a home ever since.

991
01:29:34,310 --> 01:29:36,730
<i>He doesn't even know that his wife is dead.</i>

992
01:29:36,820 --> 01:29:40,190
I was wrong about Sammy,
and I was wrong about his wife.

993
01:29:40,280 --> 01:29:42,200
She wasn't interested in the money.

994
01:29:42,280 --> 01:29:44,450
She just needed to understand his problem.

995
01:29:44,530 --> 01:29:47,950
<i>His brain didn't respond to conditioning.
But he wasn't a con man.</i>

996
01:29:48,040 --> 01:29:51,460
<i>When she looked into his eyes,
she thought he could be the same person.</i>

997
01:29:51,540 --> 01:29:53,920
<i>When I looked into his eyes,
I thought I saw recognition.</i>

998
01:29:54,000 --> 01:29:56,130
Now I know. You fake it.

999
01:29:56,210 --> 01:29:59,050
If you think you're supposed to
recognize somebody, you just pretend to.

1000
01:29:59,130 --> 01:30:01,800
<i>You bluff it to get a pat
on the head from the doctors.</i>

1001
01:30:02,430 --> 01:30:04,680
You bluff it to seem less of a freak.

1002
01:30:08,310 --> 01:30:10,020
What drug dealer?

1003
01:30:35,420 --> 01:30:38,540
- Hey, Lenny, how you doing?
- It's private back here.

1004
01:30:38,630 --> 01:30:41,630
- It's okay. We know each other. Right, kid?
- How did you know I was in here?

1005
01:30:41,720 --> 01:30:43,720
The Jag's out front.
Should have put it around back.

1006
01:30:43,800 --> 01:30:47,300
What are you still doing here, Lenny?
There's plenty of tattoo parlors up north.

1007
01:30:47,390 --> 01:30:49,890
I guess I wanted to get something down
before it slipped my mind.

1008
01:30:49,970 --> 01:30:52,430
- Give me the keys. I'll move it.
- It'll be all right for a minute.

1009
01:30:52,520 --> 01:30:54,020
Wait out there.

1010
01:30:54,850 --> 01:30:57,440
Give me a minute.
I gotta get something for you.

1011
01:31:01,190 --> 01:31:05,240
Fact six: Car license SG 137I U.

1012
01:31:11,290 --> 01:31:13,540
Look. Wait a minute, will ya?

1013
01:31:17,040 --> 01:31:19,080
- We gotta get you out of here.
- Why?

1014
01:31:19,170 --> 01:31:22,460
Man. Come on, Leonard.
How many times I gotta tell you?

1015
01:31:22,550 --> 01:31:24,920
- It's not safe for you to hang around here anymore.
- Why not?

1016
01:31:25,010 --> 01:31:26,930
Because that cop's looking for you.

1017
01:31:27,010 --> 01:31:29,600
I gotta get you a new identity,
some new clothes.

1018
01:31:29,680 --> 01:31:32,310
A different car would do for now.
So put these on.

1019
01:31:32,390 --> 01:31:33,770
What cop?

1020
01:31:34,980 --> 01:31:37,940
He's a bad cop. He's the one
that checked you into the Discount Inn.

1021
01:31:38,020 --> 01:31:41,860
He's been calling you for days, telling you shit,
slipping envelopes under your door. Shit like that.

1022
01:31:41,940 --> 01:31:44,650
- How do you know this?
- He told me. He thinks it's funny.

1023
01:31:44,740 --> 01:31:46,740
- He's been laughing at you.
- You're full of shit.

1024
01:31:46,820 --> 01:31:49,660
I'm not. He knows you're no good on
the phone, so he's been calling you.

1025
01:31:49,740 --> 01:31:51,740
Sometimes you don't answer the phone...

1026
01:31:51,830 --> 01:31:54,620
so he slips shit under your door to scare
you into answering the phone again...

1027
01:31:54,700 --> 01:31:57,370
giving you a line of crap about John G.
being some local drug dealer.

1028
01:31:57,460 --> 01:32:00,710
- Jimmy Grants.
- Who's Jimmy Grants?

1029
01:32:00,790 --> 01:32:02,750
Leonard, Jimmy's the drug dealer.

1030
01:32:02,840 --> 01:32:05,130
The cop wants to know
how his operation's run.

1031
01:32:05,220 --> 01:32:07,220
He's got some score in mind.
Somehow you're involved.

1032
01:32:07,300 --> 01:32:08,970
Uh-huh. How do you know him?

1033
01:32:10,050 --> 01:32:14,770
I'm a snitch. He's a cop from out of town.
The local boys put us together.

1034
01:32:14,850 --> 01:32:17,180
If he knew I was helping you,
he'd fucking kill me.

1035
01:32:17,270 --> 01:32:21,060
So take these clothes, put them on
and get the fuck out of here.

1036
01:32:21,150 --> 01:32:23,770
Come on, Leonard. Just go.

1037
01:32:44,420 --> 01:32:46,380
You are full of shit.

1038
01:32:48,090 --> 01:32:50,260
"Come by after. Natalie."

1039
01:32:50,340 --> 01:32:51,840
"Ferdy's Bar."

1040
01:33:34,680 --> 01:33:36,010
Hey, Jimmy.

1041
01:33:39,060 --> 01:33:41,850
I'm sorry.
I thought you were somebody else.

1042
01:33:42,520 --> 01:33:43,850
Sorry.

1043
01:33:44,690 --> 01:33:45,940
That's okay.

1044
01:34:00,120 --> 01:34:03,370
So this Jimmy Grants deals drugs out
of the bar where his girlfriend works?

1045
01:34:04,210 --> 01:34:06,710
But he's not gonna bring her along.
He'll come by himself, right?

1046
01:34:08,050 --> 01:34:11,010
I always figured the drugs angle
would be the best way to get him.

1047
01:34:12,050 --> 01:34:15,220
No, Officer.
I'm as ready as I'll ever be.

1048
01:34:15,930 --> 01:34:18,470
You're in the lobby?
What do you look like?

1049
01:34:19,770 --> 01:34:21,730
I'll be right there.

1050
01:35:03,850 --> 01:35:04,770
Lenny.

1051
01:35:07,900 --> 01:35:09,110
Officer Gammell.

1052
01:35:11,650 --> 01:35:14,360
Yeah. Come on.

1053
01:35:30,880 --> 01:35:33,340
- Smile.
- Not here.

1054
01:35:34,670 --> 01:35:35,970
Over here.

1055
01:35:41,640 --> 01:35:44,640
- Is it Officer or Lieutenant Gammell?
- You know what?

1056
01:35:44,730 --> 01:35:46,940
Don't write Gammell, just Teddy.

1057
01:35:47,600 --> 01:35:49,650
- Why?
- I'm undercover.

1058
01:35:52,480 --> 01:35:54,900
This is the directions where he's going.

1059
01:35:54,990 --> 01:35:58,030
- My number's on the bottom if you need me.
- You're not coming?

1060
01:35:58,110 --> 01:36:00,030
No. It wouldn't be appropriate.

1061
01:36:04,580 --> 01:36:07,660
Nice picture. I look thin.

1062
01:36:11,380 --> 01:36:12,670
Hey, Lenny.

1063
01:36:13,340 --> 01:36:14,760
Make him beg.

1064
01:37:37,840 --> 01:37:39,090
Teddy!

1065
01:37:42,300 --> 01:37:43,800
Hey, Teddy!

1066
01:37:50,770 --> 01:37:51,940
Jimmy.

1067
01:37:53,730 --> 01:37:56,310
- What the fuck are you doing here?
- You Jimmy Grants?

1068
01:37:56,400 --> 01:37:58,400
Expecting any otherJimmys out here,
Memory Man?

1069
01:37:58,480 --> 01:38:02,740
- Do you remember me?
- Yeah, I remember you.

1070
01:38:02,820 --> 01:38:05,240
Where the fuck's Teddy?

1071
01:38:05,320 --> 01:38:06,030
Well?

1072
01:38:10,160 --> 01:38:12,960
Motherfuck... Fuckin' retard!

1073
01:38:15,080 --> 01:38:18,130
- Strip.
- You're making a big fucking mistake, pal.

1074
01:38:18,210 --> 01:38:19,500
Strip!

1075
01:38:21,590 --> 01:38:24,180
My associates are not
the kind of people you wanna piss off.

1076
01:38:24,260 --> 01:38:25,840
Don't say anything else.

1077
01:38:25,930 --> 01:38:28,350
- I knew I couldn't trust that fuck!
- Take it off.

1078
01:38:30,980 --> 01:38:32,520
Cocksucker.

1079
01:38:33,600 --> 01:38:35,400
Your pants too.

1080
01:38:36,360 --> 01:38:38,320
- Why?
- I don't wanna get blood on them.

1081
01:38:40,400 --> 01:38:42,400
Wait.
Did he tell you what I was bringing?

1082
01:38:42,490 --> 01:38:46,410
- Take your fuckin' pants off!
- I've got 200 grand stashed in the car!

1083
01:38:46,490 --> 01:38:49,200
- Just take it!
- You think you can bargain with me?

1084
01:38:49,290 --> 01:38:51,660
- Take the money and walk away!
- I don't want your fuckin' money.

1085
01:38:52,710 --> 01:38:54,160
Then what?

1086
01:38:54,710 --> 01:38:58,380
- What do you want from me?
- I want my fuckin' life back!

1087
01:40:28,970 --> 01:40:30,180
Sammy.

1088
01:40:36,980 --> 01:40:39,020
He said "Sammy."
How does he know about Sammy?

1089
01:40:39,100 --> 01:40:40,480
Oh, fuck.

1090
01:41:01,080 --> 01:41:03,080
What have I done?

1091
01:41:04,960 --> 01:41:07,670
Mister, I need help.
There's a guy in here, he's hurt bad.

1092
01:41:07,760 --> 01:41:10,010
- We gotta get him to a doctor.
- All right.

1093
01:41:11,800 --> 01:41:14,100
I don't know what happened.
I've got this memory thing.

1094
01:41:14,180 --> 01:41:16,390
- Do I know you?
- No. Don't worry. I'm a cop.

1095
01:41:17,220 --> 01:41:20,020
- Is he still breathing?
- I don't know. Maybe.

1096
01:41:20,100 --> 01:41:22,650
What the hell were you guys
doing down here?

1097
01:41:24,190 --> 01:41:26,270
I don't remember.
I have this condition.

1098
01:41:26,360 --> 01:41:29,070
I hope it's not as serious as his,
'cause this guy's dead.

1099
01:41:29,150 --> 01:41:31,700
Ow! Lenny! That shit kills!

1100
01:41:31,780 --> 01:41:35,330
So you remember me now, huh?
You are a fuckin' cop.

1101
01:41:35,410 --> 01:41:38,240
Yeah. And I'm the guy
that helped you find him.

1102
01:41:38,330 --> 01:41:40,210
Get up. Get up.

1103
01:41:40,290 --> 01:41:42,330
Lenny, you got the wrong idea.

1104
01:41:45,040 --> 01:41:47,090
Who is that? He knew me.

1105
01:41:47,170 --> 01:41:49,800
Of course he did. He raped your wife.
He fucked up your brain.

1106
01:41:49,880 --> 01:41:51,930
Bullshit. He's not the guy.

1107
01:41:52,010 --> 01:41:56,350
His name is James F. Grants.
John G. Check your tattoos.

1108
01:41:56,430 --> 01:41:58,850
- What was he bringing the 200 grand for?
- What?

1109
01:42:00,430 --> 01:42:03,230
- What was it for?
- A load of amphetamines I told him I had.

1110
01:42:03,310 --> 01:42:06,770
- Is this a drug deal?
- No. Yeah, that and your thing.

1111
01:42:06,860 --> 01:42:10,490
Look, Leonard, Jimmy's your guy. I just
figured we'd make a few dollars on the side.

1112
01:42:10,570 --> 01:42:14,200
- How did he know me?
- The Discount Inn. He dealt out of there.

1113
01:42:14,280 --> 01:42:17,580
The guy at the front desk let him know
if anybody came snooping around.

1114
01:42:17,660 --> 01:42:20,200
He called Jimmy the minute he saw you
taking a picture of the dump.

1115
01:42:20,290 --> 01:42:22,660
- You're fucking using me.
- No! You get half!

1116
01:42:22,750 --> 01:42:25,380
He knew about Sammy!
Why would I tell him about fuckin' Sammy?

1117
01:42:25,460 --> 01:42:28,840
You tell everybody about Sammy,
everybody who'll listen.

1118
01:42:28,920 --> 01:42:31,050
"Remember SammyJankis?"
"Remember SammyJankis?"

1119
01:42:31,130 --> 01:42:34,050
Great story.
Gets better every time you tell it.

1120
01:42:35,010 --> 01:42:36,930
So you lie to yourself to be happy.

1121
01:42:37,010 --> 01:42:39,060
There's nothing wrong with that.
We all do it.

1122
01:42:39,140 --> 01:42:42,270
Who cares if there's a few little details
you'd rather not remember?

1123
01:42:44,730 --> 01:42:47,060
- What the fuck are you talking about?
- I don't know.

1124
01:42:47,860 --> 01:42:49,770
Your wife surviving the assault.

1125
01:42:50,570 --> 01:42:52,490
Her not believing your condition.

1126
01:42:52,570 --> 01:42:56,740
The torment and pain and anguish
tearing her up inside.

1127
01:42:57,320 --> 01:42:58,620
The insulin.

1128
01:42:59,910 --> 01:43:02,620
That's Sammy, not me.
I told you about Sammy.

1129
01:43:02,710 --> 01:43:05,710
Yeah, right.
Like you tell yourself over and over again.

1130
01:43:05,790 --> 01:43:07,790
Conditioning yourself to remember.

1131
01:43:07,880 --> 01:43:10,460
- Learning through repetition.
- Sammy let his wife kill herself.

1132
01:43:10,550 --> 01:43:15,590
- Sammy ended up in an institution.
- Sammy was a con man, a faker.

1133
01:43:15,680 --> 01:43:17,840
I never said that Sammy was faking.

1134
01:43:18,430 --> 01:43:20,890
You exposed him for what he was... a fraud.

1135
01:43:20,970 --> 01:43:22,930
But I was wrong.
That's the whole point.

1136
01:43:24,600 --> 01:43:27,350
- See, Sammy's wife came to me.
- Sammy didn't have a wife.

1137
01:43:30,110 --> 01:43:32,440
It was <i>your</i> wife who had diabetes.

1138
01:43:38,820 --> 01:43:39,820
Ouch.

1139
01:43:42,450 --> 01:43:44,120
My wife wasn't diabetic.

1140
01:43:45,120 --> 01:43:46,540
You sure?

1141
01:43:51,340 --> 01:43:54,460
- Ouch. Cut it out.
- She wasn't diabetic.

1142
01:43:55,470 --> 01:43:59,260
You think I don't know my own wife?
What the fuck is wrong with you?

1143
01:43:59,350 --> 01:44:02,760
I guess I can only make you remember
the things you wanna be true.

1144
01:44:02,850 --> 01:44:05,230
- Like old Jimmy down there.
- He's not the right guy.

1145
01:44:05,310 --> 01:44:07,480
He was to you.

1146
01:44:07,560 --> 01:44:10,980
Come on. You got your revenge.
Enjoy it while you still remember.

1147
01:44:11,070 --> 01:44:13,570
What difference does it make
whether he was your guy or not?

1148
01:44:13,650 --> 01:44:16,280
- It makes all the difference.
- Why? You're never gonna know.

1149
01:44:16,360 --> 01:44:17,650
- Yes, I will.
- No, you won't.

1150
01:44:17,740 --> 01:44:19,200
I will. Somehow I'll know.

1151
01:44:19,280 --> 01:44:21,700
- You won't remember!
- When it's done, I will know. It'll be different.

1152
01:44:21,780 --> 01:44:25,700
I thought so too.
In fact, I was sure of it, but you didn't!

1153
01:44:28,500 --> 01:44:31,750
That's right. The real John G.

1154
01:44:31,840 --> 01:44:35,420
I helped you find him over a year ago.
He's already dead.

1155
01:44:35,510 --> 01:44:38,380
- Don't lie to me anymore.
- Look, Lenny.

1156
01:44:39,010 --> 01:44:41,890
I was the cop assigned to your wife's case.
I believed you.

1157
01:44:41,970 --> 01:44:44,510
I thought you deserved
a chance for revenge.

1158
01:44:44,600 --> 01:44:47,890
I'm the one that helped you find the
other guy in your bathroom that night...

1159
01:44:47,980 --> 01:44:50,310
the guy that cracked your skull
and fucked your wife.

1160
01:44:50,400 --> 01:44:52,860
We found him. You killed him.

1161
01:44:54,530 --> 01:44:59,860
But you didn't remember.
So I helped you start looking again...

1162
01:44:59,950 --> 01:45:02,200
looking for the guy you already killed.

1163
01:45:02,740 --> 01:45:04,490
Yeah? So who was he?

1164
01:45:04,580 --> 01:45:06,950
Just some guy.
Does it even matter who?

1165
01:45:07,710 --> 01:45:11,580
No reason, Lenny. No conspiracy.
Just bad fucking luck.

1166
01:45:12,790 --> 01:45:16,550
Couple ofjunkies too strung out
to realize your wife didn't live alone.

1167
01:45:17,720 --> 01:45:21,510
But when you killed him,
I was so convinced that you'd remember.

1168
01:45:22,090 --> 01:45:24,050
But it didn't stick.

1169
01:45:24,140 --> 01:45:26,890
Like nothing ever sticks.
Like this won't stick.

1170
01:45:31,560 --> 01:45:36,190
I took that picture...
just when you did it.

1171
01:45:38,190 --> 01:45:40,110
Look how happy you are.

1172
01:45:41,450 --> 01:45:43,200
I wanted to see that face again.

1173
01:45:43,280 --> 01:45:46,080
- Gee, thanks.
- Fuck you.

1174
01:45:46,160 --> 01:45:49,910
I gave you a reason to live,
and you were more than happy to help.

1175
01:45:50,000 --> 01:45:54,170
You don't want the truth.
You make up your own truth.

1176
01:45:54,250 --> 01:45:56,210
Like your police file.

1177
01:45:57,050 --> 01:46:00,050
It was complete when I gave it to you.
Who took out the 12 pages?

1178
01:46:00,130 --> 01:46:02,680
- You, probably.
- No, it wasn't me. See, it was you.

1179
01:46:02,760 --> 01:46:06,470
- Why would I do that?
- To create a puzzle you could never solve.

1180
01:46:06,560 --> 01:46:08,470
You know how many towns?

1181
01:46:08,560 --> 01:46:10,730
How manyJohn G.'s orJames G.'s?

