01:46:10,810 --> 01:46:12,850
Shit, Lenny. I'm a fucking John G.

1183
01:46:12,940 --> 01:46:16,190
- Your name is Teddy.
- My mother calls me Teddy.

1184
01:46:16,270 --> 01:46:19,150
My name's John Edward Gammell.

1185
01:46:19,240 --> 01:46:20,280
Cheer up.

1186
01:46:20,360 --> 01:46:23,110
There's plenty ofJohn G.'s for us to find.

1187
01:46:26,490 --> 01:46:28,910
All you do is moan.

1188
01:46:28,990 --> 01:46:31,330
I'm the one that has to live
with what you've done.

1189
01:46:31,410 --> 01:46:33,120
I'm the one that put it all together.

1190
01:46:33,210 --> 01:46:37,880
You wander around, you're playing
detective. You're living a dream, kid.

1191
01:46:37,960 --> 01:46:42,050
A dead wife to pine for.
A sense of purpose to your life.

1192
01:46:42,130 --> 01:46:45,470
A romantic quest that you wouldn't end
even if I wasn't in the picture.

1193
01:46:46,760 --> 01:46:49,930
- I should kill you.
- Quit it. Lenny, come on.

1194
01:46:50,020 --> 01:46:53,020
You're not a killer.
That's why you're so good at it.

1195
01:46:56,560 --> 01:46:59,320
What are you doing?
You know what time it is?

1196
01:46:59,400 --> 01:47:01,480
It's beer o'clock. I'm buying.

1197
01:47:03,490 --> 01:47:04,610
Fuck.

1198
01:47:14,710 --> 01:47:15,830
I'm not a killer.

1199
01:47:17,130 --> 01:47:19,670
I'm just someone who wanted
to make things right.

1200
01:47:25,720 --> 01:47:28,090
Can I just let myself forget
what you've told me?

1201
01:47:45,320 --> 01:47:48,700
Can I just let myself forget
what you made me do?

1202
01:48:02,960 --> 01:48:04,710
You think I just want
another puzzle to solve?

1203
01:48:05,550 --> 01:48:07,720
AnotherJohn G. to look for?

1204
01:48:08,930 --> 01:48:10,800
You're a John G.

1205
01:48:12,510 --> 01:48:14,600
So you can be myJohn G.

1206
01:48:23,070 --> 01:48:25,190
Do I lie to myself to be happy?

1207
01:48:26,490 --> 01:48:28,240
In your case, Teddy...

1208
01:48:29,370 --> 01:48:31,280
yes, I will.

1209
01:48:44,420 --> 01:48:46,510
Hey, that's not your car!

1210
01:48:46,590 --> 01:48:49,180
- It is now.
- Jesus Christ, you can't take it!

1211
01:48:49,260 --> 01:48:52,180
- Why not?
- Because the guy you just killed owns it!

1212
01:48:52,260 --> 01:48:53,970
Somebody'll recognize it!

1213
01:48:55,430 --> 01:48:58,520
I think I'd rather be mistaken
for a dead guy than a killer.

1214
01:48:59,480 --> 01:49:01,980
I might hang on to this for a while.

1215
01:49:02,820 --> 01:49:04,110
Lenny.

1216
01:49:06,150 --> 01:49:08,650
Will you help me find the keys?

1217
01:49:08,740 --> 01:49:10,490
Help me find my keys.

1218
01:49:32,760 --> 01:49:36,060
I have to believe in a world
outside my own mind.

1219
01:49:36,140 --> 01:49:38,310
I have to believe that
my actions still have meaning...

1220
01:49:38,390 --> 01:49:40,350
even if I can't remember them.

1221
01:49:42,520 --> 01:49:45,190
I have to believe
that when my eyes are closed...

1222
01:49:45,270 --> 01:49:47,360
the world's still here.

1223
01:49:48,570 --> 01:49:50,990
Do I believe the world's still here?

1224
01:49:53,910 --> 01:49:55,490
Is it still out there?

1225
01:49:59,330 --> 01:50:00,330
Yeah.

1226
01:50:02,710 --> 01:50:05,500
We all need mirrors
to remind ourselves who we are.

1227
01:50:07,840 --> 01:50:09,550
I'm no different.

1228
01:50:22,850 --> 01:50:24,650
Now, where was I?

